  <para id="fs-id1931773">A box with a mass of 2.0 kg rests on one end of a seesaw. The seesaw is 6.0 m long, and we can assume it has negligible mass. Approximately what angular momentum will the box have if someone with a mass of 65 kg sits on the other end of the seesaw quickly, with a velocity of 1.2 m/s?</para><list id="fs-id1838365" list-type="enumerated" number-style="lower-alpha"><item>702 kg•m<sup>2</sup>/s</item>
