  <para id="fs-id1619499">Angular momentum is directly proportional to the torque exerted on the object. In the case of the electric screwdriver, the torque provided at each speed is probably unknown. Angular momentum is also the product of rotational inertia and angular velocity. It would be possible to calculate it from these two values. </para>
  <para id="fs-id1481256">Although it is an approximation, a screw can be thought of as a solid cylinder, spinning about the cylinder axis. From <link document="m55186" target-id="fs-id1838666">Figure 10.12</link>, the rotational inertia of such a shape can be found using 
